<p>Within five years, the open-source AI will have raised the GDP of the poorest countries. That is the premise of my conversation with Emad Mostaque<a id="footnote-anchor-1" href="#footnote-1">1</a>, founder and CEO of Stability AI, one of the companies behind Stable Diffusion.</p><iframe src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/enp8lM3DwGc?rel=0&amp;autoplay=0&amp;showinfo=0&amp;enablejsapi=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true" width="728" height="409" sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups" loading="lazy"></iframe><p>Earlier this year, Goldman Sachs published a research brief titled “The Potentially Large Effect of Artificial Intelligence on Economic Growth”<a id="footnote-anchor-2" href="#footnote-2">2</a>, in which the authors explore the future of the labour market. The study suggested that global productivity could see an impressive uptick, ultimately boosting global GDP by 7%. </p><p>In this conversation, we discuss what would need to be true to make this happen. Open-source AI is one part of the answer. </p><figure><a href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6ba586b3-29c8-4133-b0ab-35f16745a5bd_1482x996.png" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/CCo3T6UunNlNAkbo2vgZsY- 424w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/D-ZrCJKM1TAQMmDM9xr-3vEfPghB-jNBDyEIpbBtoZo=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd184NDgsY19saW1pdCxmX3dlYnAscV9hdXRvOmdvb2QsZmxfcHJvZ3Jlc3NpdmU6c3RlZXAvaHR0cHMlM0ElMkYlMkZzdWJzdGFjay1wb3N0LW1lZGlhLnMzLmFtYXpvbmF3cy5jb20lMkZwdWJsaWMlMkZpbWFnZXMlMkY2YmE1ODZiMy0yOWM4LTQxMzMtYjBhYi0zNWYxNjc0NWE1YmRfMTQ4Mng5OTYucG5n 848w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/ftvQIuzswpMl_ 1272w, https://reader.miniflux.app/proxy/gn066KWGLwPAIMSS08azSu2ilg8TtGOL-vWAQikbmsU=/aHR0cHM6Ly9zdWJzdGFja2Nkbi5jb20vaW1hZ2UvZmV0Y2gvd18xN